Anthrax, livestock - South Africa (Mpumalanga) 20010220.0327
Date: 23 March, 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: The People, Nairobi [edited

An outbreak of the highly contagious disease anthrax has been reported in
parts of Murang'a District (Central Kenya). Confirming the outbreak, the
district veterinary officer, Emman Kibaara, said 5 cows had died of the
disease by early this week. Other reports claimed that at least 10 cows
had succumbed to the disease in the past week.
Kibaara further disclosed that 4 people have been infected while
slaughtering the infected animals. Kibaara [said that their condition is
improving after receiving treatment at Murang'a district hospital.
Kiharu District Officer Samuel Njoora named the affected villages:
Kiambuki, Gakuyu, Githanga, and Kaweru.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
